WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:00:24.733 --> 00:00:27.902
<i>So. what did you do
with your last night in Florida?</i>

3
00:00:27.903 --> 00:00:32.031
It was awesome sauce.
My boys gave me a little bit of a sendoff

4
00:00:32.032 --> 00:00:33.824
'cause I'm not gonna
be back till Christmas.

5
00:00:33.825 --> 00:00:35.076
- Your "boys"?
- Yeah.

6
00:00:35.077 --> 00:00:36.577
- Who are your boys?
- You know.

7
00:00:36.578 --> 00:00:37.870
My boys.

8
00:00:37.871 --> 00:00:39.372
Sam. Cliff.

9
00:00:39.373 --> 00:00:40.540
Norm.

10
00:00:40.541 --> 00:00:41.958
So. the cast of <i>Cheers.</i>

11
00:00:41.959 --> 00:00:43.376
I did not know you knew that show.

12
00:00:43.377 --> 00:00:44.710
Mm-hmm. was Coach there?

13
00:00:44.711 --> 00:00:47.505
Unfortunately. Coach passed.
Season three.

14
00:00:47.506 --> 00:00:48.966
I'm sorry.

15
00:00:50.300 --> 00:00:52.635
Look at this house they're giving me.

16
00:00:52.636 --> 00:00:53.886
Wow.

17
00:00:53.887 --> 00:00:55.972
Oh! A gift basket.

18
00:00:55.973 --> 00:00:57.557
They asked me what
your favorite booze was.

19
00:00:57.558 --> 00:00:59.600
Oh! Thank you. honey.

20
00:00:59.601 --> 00:01:01.811
Didn't buy it. just replied to a text.

21
00:01:01.812 --> 00:01:03.188
Well. you remembered.

22
00:01:04.189 --> 00:01:06.232
Oh.

23
00:01:06.233 --> 00:01:08.442
This place is way too big for one person.

24
00:01:08.443 --> 00:01:09.569
I'm not moving in with you. Dad.

25
00:01:09.570 --> 00:01:10.987
- I wasn't thinking that.
- Yes. you were.

26
00:01:10.988 --> 00:01:13.448
Yes. I was.
We'd have so much fun!

27
00:01:14.449 --> 00:01:15.825
Oh. I like this.

28
00:01:15.826 --> 00:01:17.493
- Mm!
- What do you think?

29
00:01:17.494 --> 00:01:19.120
- Yeah.
- Could I wear this under a blazer?

30
00:01:19.121 --> 00:01:20.205
- Never do that.
- No?

31
00:01:21.498 --> 00:01:23.708
Dad. we have to talk about something.

32
00:01:23.709 --> 00:01:24.710
Oh!

33
00:01:25.919 --> 00:01:28.588
Dill pickle-flavored Corn Nuts?
Is that regional?

34
00:01:28.589 --> 00:01:29.631
I don't know.

35
00:01:31.925 --> 00:01:35.511
It's taken me a while
to get out of Mom's shadow.

36
00:01:35.512 --> 00:01:38.389
And you're here now.

37
00:01:38.390 --> 00:01:40.683
- Mm-hmm.
- Which I've decided is great.

38
00:01:40.684 --> 00:01:42.393
Ooh! That took a nice turn.

39
00:01:42.394 --> 00:01:43.853
I've been trying
to get you out of your rut

40
00:01:43.854 --> 00:01:47.231
since you and Mom split up.
and this is definitely that.

41
00:01:47.232 --> 00:01:50.443
- Mm-hmm.
- But with my marriage collapsing

42
00:01:50.444 --> 00:01:52.403
and my suspension...

43
00:01:52.404 --> 00:01:54.363
I can barely take care of myself.

44
00:01:54.364 --> 00:01:57.283
So. if I feel like I need
to take care of you. I...

45
00:01:57.284 --> 00:01:59.118
We need to give each other

46
00:01:59.119 --> 00:02:01.287
- some space. you know?
- Mm-hmm.

47
00:02:01.288 --> 00:02:02.872
Jesus Christ. just eat them.

48
00:02:02.873 --> 00:02:05.541
Sorry. They taste like crunchy pickles.

49
00:02:05.542 --> 00:02:06.752
Mm-hmm.

50
00:02:08.754 --> 00:02:09.920
Mm!

51
00:02:09.921 --> 00:02:11.298
- Okay. Sorry.
- Okay.

52
00:02:12.424 --> 00:02:14.217
- I have my own life...
- Hold on. One more.

53
00:02:17.429 --> 00:02:18.764
- As you were saying.
- Okay.

54
00:02:19.723 --> 00:02:21.349
- I have my own life here.
- Mm-hmm.

55
00:02:21.350 --> 00:02:23.476
I can't have you holding my hand.

56
00:02:23.477 --> 00:02:25.227
Got it. You can fight your own battles.

57
00:02:25.228 --> 00:02:29.482
And if you can't fight them by yourself.
we will fight them together. hand in hand.

58
00:02:29.483 --> 00:02:31.359
- It was a joke.
- Yeah. I'm leaving now.

59
00:02:31.360 --> 00:02:33.110
- Okay.
- And I'm taking the Toblerone.

60
00:02:33.111 --> 00:02:35.405
And honey. thank you for this.

61
00:02:36.448 --> 00:02:38.699
Also. I wasn't serious
about living together.

62
00:02:38.700 --> 00:02:40.618
Oh. really? I was just thinking

63
00:02:40.619 --> 00:02:42.536
how the dead hockey coach's
house is kinda lonely.

64
00:02:42.537 --> 00:02:44.205
and it might be fun to crash here

65
00:02:44.206 --> 00:02:45.498
- for a couple weeks...
- Do it!

66
00:02:45.499 --> 00:02:47.249
Order pizza. I will get a...

67
00:02:47.250 --> 00:02:48.876
Oh. that was not nice.

68
00:02:48.877 --> 00:02:50.836
- That was not a nice thing to do.
- Love you.

69
00:02:50.837 --> 00:02:52.130
I love you. too.

70
00:03:40.846 --> 00:03:43.264
Oh. hey! Hey. new neighbor!

71
00:03:43.265 --> 00:03:44.765
It's so weird. Remember?

72
00:03:44.766 --> 00:03:46.350
Your friend was supposed
to live in this house.

73
00:03:46.351 --> 00:03:48.185
I remember.

74
00:03:48.186 --> 00:03:50.187
Calm down. I'm not mad at you.

75
00:03:50.188 --> 00:03:51.648
Thanks. God.

76
00:03:53.942 --> 00:03:55.818
Can I walk with you?

77
00:03:55.819 --> 00:03:57.862
I got the first-day jitters
and I don't know

78
00:03:57.863 --> 00:03:59.864
- where anything is.
- Come on.

79
00:03:59.865 --> 00:04:01.490
Thank you.

80
00:04:01.491 --> 00:04:03.325
What's up with the shoes?
You going to prom?

81
00:04:03.326 --> 00:04:05.327
Oh. I knew they were too shiny.

82
00:04:05.328 --> 00:04:06.495
- Whoa.
- You okay?

83
00:04:06.496 --> 00:04:08.330
- Yep. I'm good.
- Okay.

84
00:04:08.331 --> 00:04:10.458
Hey. you got a minute
to help me with something?

85
00:04:10.459 --> 00:04:11.792
Yeah. of course. You name it.

86
00:04:11.793 --> 00:04:13.794
- Okay.
- Ooh! That is cool.

87
00:04:13.795 --> 00:04:15.255
You should get one.

88
00:04:16.256 --> 00:04:18.340
I need to lock in my summer internship.

89
00:04:18.341 --> 00:04:20.134
I don't think you know
how much I'm freaking out.

90
00:04:20.135 --> 00:04:22.052
I mean. you don't exactly
sound so freaked out.

91
00:04:22.053 --> 00:04:23.888
Why don't you give me
something with a little gusto?

92
00:04:23.889 --> 00:04:25.556
- How are you feeling?
- I'm not sleeping.

93
00:04:25.557 --> 00:04:27.099
- At all? You're stressed!
- I'm stressed!

94
00:04:27.100 --> 00:04:28.851
- I'm stressed!
- Guys. guys. guys. guys. guys. please.

95
00:04:28.852 --> 00:04:30.519
I'm trying to work on my book here.

96
00:04:30.520 --> 00:04:34.857
Oh. my God. I am so sorry
for talking in my own apartment.

97
00:04:34.858 --> 00:04:35.901
I hate him.

98
00:04:36.485 --> 00:04:38.110
- We will keep it down.
- Thank you.

99
00:04:38.111 --> 00:04:39.612
I need an advisor with pull.

100
00:04:39.613 --> 00:04:41.197
I should just ask President Mann.

101
00:04:41.198 --> 00:04:42.990
- He's at the gym all the time.
- Right!

102
00:04:42.991 --> 00:04:44.575
Oh. you and Walt.

103
00:04:44.576 --> 00:04:46.619
That's really not...
That's not ideal for me.

104
00:04:46.620 --> 00:04:48.037
Ideal for you?

105
00:04:48.038 --> 00:04:49.246
Yeah.

106
00:04:49.247 --> 00:04:50.831
Permission to be frank?

107
00:04:50.832 --> 00:04:53.375
Break up. Let's wrap this up. Go home!

108
00:04:53.376 --> 00:04:55.294
It's just that I have been
in the spotlight

109
00:04:55.295 --> 00:04:56.754
quite a lot lately. and I think

110
00:04:56.755 --> 00:04:58.547
maybe in lieu of drawing
more attention to us...

111
00:04:58.548 --> 00:05:00.007
She just rolled her eyes
at me saying "in lieu."

112
00:05:00.008 --> 00:05:02.385
Educated people say "in lieu." Mo.

113
00:05:04.638 --> 00:05:08.474
My editor is calling me every single day
asking to see new pages on this.

114
00:05:08.475 --> 00:05:11.936
This book is not just for me.
it's for our child's future. alright?

115
00:05:11.937 --> 00:05:13.813
So. I think it would behoove us
to create conditions

116
00:05:13.814 --> 00:05:15.689
under which I can succeed.

117
00:05:15.690 --> 00:05:19.693
Walt. he is. like.
the biggest gossip on campus. alright?

118
00:05:19.694 --> 00:05:21.987
And the last thing
that we need is that man

119
00:05:21.988 --> 00:05:23.490
rooting around in our lives.

120
00:05:24.699 --> 00:05:27.368
'Kay. fine. I won't ask him.

121
00:05:27.369 --> 00:05:28.370
Thank you.

122
00:05:31.248 --> 00:05:35.209
So. you think it's okay to just hire him.
even though you already promised

123
00:05:35.210 --> 00:05:37.336
the Writer-In-Residence gig
to my friend Ruby?

124
00:05:37.337 --> 00:05:39.171
If this is what you meant
by helping. I don't love it.

125
00:05:39.172 --> 00:05:41.632
Hiring Greg was
a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity.

126
00:05:41.633 --> 00:05:42.925
Your friend can do it next semester.

127
00:05:42.926 --> 00:05:45.386
Maybe that'll give her time
to write something someone's heard of.

128
00:05:45.387 --> 00:05:48.097
Ruby won the Baillie Gifford Prize
in nonfiction.

129
00:05:48.098 --> 00:05:50.099
- We all have our resumes.
- Look.

130
00:05:50.100 --> 00:05:54.687
Walt said that I had to take the job
or Katie was gonna lose hers.

131
00:05:54.688 --> 00:05:56.897
And I would appreciate it
if we'd just keep that between us.

132
00:05:56.898 --> 00:05:58.774
- because Katie would kill me.
- Of course.

133
00:05:58.775 --> 00:06:01.527
Better watch your back. Greg.
'cause he might stab you in it.

134
00:06:01.528 --> 00:06:03.487
You understand this isn't
even about her friend.

135
00:06:03.488 --> 00:06:05.698
This is about the <i>Review.</i>

136
00:06:05.699 --> 00:06:07.241
I don't know what the <i>Review</i> is.

137
00:06:07.242 --> 00:06:09.869
- That is a shitty thing to say.
- Then I take it back. I do.

138
00:06:09.870 --> 00:06:13.122
We're supposed to be friends. Walt.
and you just tossed it aside.

139
00:06:13.123 --> 00:06:16.250
You need to handle your job
with a little more grace and sensitivity.

140
00:06:16.251 --> 00:06:18.795
Do you know why I am
so deeply drawn to Greg?

141
00:06:19.880 --> 00:06:21.463
You don't... That's not necessary.

142
00:06:21.464 --> 00:06:22.923
Because he is the only one around here

143
00:06:22.924 --> 00:06:25.010
who doesn't actually want
something from me.

144
00:06:27.470 --> 00:06:28.888
It's a teeny tiny violin.

145
00:06:28.889 --> 00:06:30.723
I was gonna ask what that was.

146
00:06:30.724 --> 00:06:32.558
- It is really small.
- If you would excuse us.

147
00:06:32.559 --> 00:06:34.894
I have to help Greg find his new office.

148
00:06:34.895 --> 00:06:36.353
Come. This way.

149
00:06:36.354 --> 00:06:37.522
Bye-bye.

150
00:06:41.484 --> 00:06:43.235
And here we are.

151
00:06:43.236 --> 00:06:46.739
Think I could have found this on my own.
Do I need to apologize to Dylan?

152
00:06:46.740 --> 00:06:49.325
Oh. we did nothing wrong.
She should be apologizing to us.

153
00:06:49.326 --> 00:06:51.328
Let me show you my favorite part
of this whole setup.

154
00:06:54.372 --> 00:06:56.165
Do you love it as much as I do?

155
00:06:56.166 --> 00:06:58.125
So. your office is connected to my...

156
00:06:58.126 --> 00:07:01.337
You can come by
and say hi anytime.

157
00:07:01.338 --> 00:07:03.797
- That'll be fun.
- We got a hockey game tomorrow night.

158
00:07:03.798 --> 00:07:05.049
Hired a new coach. You care to come?

159
00:07:05.050 --> 00:07:07.801
I'm not really a hockey guy.

160
00:07:07.802 --> 00:07:11.138
I wish that you had told me
that I was taking Dylan's friend's job.

161
00:07:11.139 --> 00:07:13.766
I bet Dylan's friend
wished we told her. as well.

162
00:07:13.767 --> 00:07:16.518
- Cristle!
- Emailed her and sent a box of pears.

163
00:07:16.519 --> 00:07:17.728
- Gym bag.
- Thank you.

164
00:07:17.729 --> 00:07:19.105
Oh. shower shoes.

165
00:07:22.150 --> 00:07:23.400
Door open or closed?

166
00:07:23.401 --> 00:07:25.235
Open's fine. thanks.

167
00:07:25.236 --> 00:07:26.321
Good choice.

168
00:07:31.409 --> 00:07:32.826
Wouldn't you know it?

169
00:07:32.827 --> 00:07:35.079
Those rascals were in my bag
the whole time.

170
00:07:35.080 --> 00:07:37.290
- I'll be back in a jiff.
- Okay.

171
00:07:39.834 --> 00:07:40.835
See you soon.

172
00:07:42.504 --> 00:07:43.712
Why are you making me do this?

173
00:07:43.713 --> 00:07:46.090
This is like a labor camp.
This is hell.

174
00:07:46.091 --> 00:07:48.218
- You're fine.
- I'm not. believe me.

175
00:07:49.386 --> 00:07:52.471
Be right back. Dean Riggs?

176
00:07:52.472 --> 00:07:54.848
I'm Sunny Salewski.
I'm in your Evolutionary Bio class.

177
00:07:54.849 --> 00:07:56.600
and I would like for you to be my advisor.

178
00:07:56.601 --> 00:07:58.686
Whoa. buy me a drink first.

179
00:07:58.687 --> 00:08:00.187
I'm looking for an internship

180
00:08:00.188 --> 00:08:01.772
in biotech with a focus
on health and wellness.

181
00:08:01.773 --> 00:08:05.485
Look. you seem like a beautiful
young scientist. but I can't.

182
00:08:06.319 --> 00:08:09.280
I'd explain further.
but I've been told not to by my attorney.

183
00:08:10.240 --> 00:08:11.157
Good luck.

184
00:08:12.826 --> 00:08:14.411
- Smoke break.
- You earned it.

185
00:08:15.412 --> 00:08:17.705
Young lady. If I may.

186
00:08:17.706 --> 00:08:19.456
Don't pick your advisor
based on what you think

187
00:08:19.457 --> 00:08:21.083
they can do for you.

188
00:08:21.084 --> 00:08:25.587
It should be someone with whom
you have a real connection.

189
00:08:25.588 --> 00:08:27.423
Thank you. sir.

190
00:08:27.424 --> 00:08:28.425
Onward.

191
00:08:29.384 --> 00:08:30.801
<i>Oh. I should have just asked him.</i>

192
00:08:30.802 --> 00:08:32.386
I mean. he was already advising me.

193
00:08:32.387 --> 00:08:34.722
No. no. No. darling. no. no. no.
He was eavesdropping

194
00:08:34.723 --> 00:08:36.724
and inserting himself
into your conversation.

195
00:08:36.725 --> 00:08:38.475
That is just what Walt does. trust me.

196
00:08:38.476 --> 00:08:41.395
Look. okay.
Once. totally offhand. right?

197
00:08:41.396 --> 00:08:44.857
I mentioned to Cristle
that I might someday want to have a dog.

198
00:08:44.858 --> 00:08:47.484
Next thing I knew.
Walt is in my living room

199
00:08:47.485 --> 00:08:48.570
with Roscoe.

200
00:08:49.487 --> 00:08:50.529
He'd already called him Roscoe.

201
00:08:50.530 --> 00:08:51.947
I wouldn't have called him Roscoe.

202
00:08:51.948 --> 00:08:53.574
I would have called him
something more whimsical.

203
00:08:53.575 --> 00:08:54.992
like Giuseppe.

204
00:08:54.993 --> 00:08:56.618
Okay. don't pretend you're not
in love with that dog.

205
00:08:56.619 --> 00:08:58.203
I've seen you open-mouth kissing him.

206
00:08:58.204 --> 00:09:01.582
He prefers it that way. he's Italian.

207
00:09:01.583 --> 00:09:03.751
Look. Riggs loves me. I'll speak to him.

208
00:09:03.752 --> 00:09:05.502
I'll get him to change his mind.
What are you doing?

209
00:09:05.503 --> 00:09:07.671
I am texting you a study
on the fecal matter

210
00:09:07.672 --> 00:09:08.882
in dogs' mouths.

211
00:09:09.841 --> 00:09:11.050
Shan't be reading that.

212
00:09:11.051 --> 00:09:15.179
Okay. so you can use these notes
on the Impressionists as a general guide.

213
00:09:15.180 --> 00:09:18.682
I'm sorry about the pizza sauce.
I had a pretty late night.

214
00:09:18.683 --> 00:09:20.851
Have you ever seen <i>Rick and Morty?</i>

215
00:09:20.852 --> 00:09:23.604
- Respecting boundaries by knocking.
- Take it. take it.

216
00:09:23.605 --> 00:09:24.688
Take it.

217
00:09:24.689 --> 00:09:26.607
Hi. hi. hi. hi. hi.

218
00:09:26.608 --> 00:09:28.317
I just wanted to check
to see if you looked

219
00:09:28.318 --> 00:09:30.235
at that lesson plan that I emailed.

220
00:09:30.236 --> 00:09:32.780
Hi... Oh. I'm sorry. Am I interrupting?

221
00:09:32.781 --> 00:09:36.366
A hundred percent.
This is Lily. my TA. She smokes.

222
00:09:36.367 --> 00:09:38.494
- Yes! I love it. Yay!
- Yay.

223
00:09:38.495 --> 00:09:40.079
I'm just prepping her to cover my classes.

224
00:09:40.080 --> 00:09:42.165
Oh. Okay. I can wait.

225
00:09:43.333 --> 00:09:46.335
But what time is her class?
Because mine starts in 25 minutes.

226
00:09:46.336 --> 00:09:47.795
Okay. Dad. fine.

227
00:09:47.796 --> 00:09:51.882
You know. I did take a look.
and this is way over-scheduled.

228
00:09:51.883 --> 00:09:53.967
This is giving me flashbacks
to when you were coaching

229
00:09:53.968 --> 00:09:56.637
my U8 soccer team
and you had that big binder of plays.

230
00:09:56.638 --> 00:09:59.431
- Yeah?
- Whoa. yeah. you've gotta relax.

231
00:09:59.432 --> 00:10:01.350
- Okay. alright.
- Okay. do you remember

232
00:10:01.351 --> 00:10:03.560
when you finally said screw it.
and you told us

233
00:10:03.561 --> 00:10:05.104
to just kick the ball around and have fun?

234
00:10:05.105 --> 00:10:06.438
Yeah. I remember that.

235
00:10:06.439 --> 00:10:08.607
Right. that was the first game
that we won.

236
00:10:08.608 --> 00:10:11.276
Well. the other team's goalie
was. like. four years old.

237
00:10:11.277 --> 00:10:13.153
Honey. honey. I get very nervous

238
00:10:13.154 --> 00:10:15.239
speaking in front of people
unless I have a plan.

239
00:10:15.240 --> 00:10:17.450
And I am not a rockstar teacher
like you are.

240
00:10:18.326 --> 00:10:20.202
At the moment.
I'm not any kind of teacher.

241
00:10:20.203 --> 00:10:21.620
Okay.

242
00:10:21.621 --> 00:10:23.038
You know what would cheer you up?

243
00:10:23.039 --> 00:10:26.125
There's a hockey game tomorrow night.
You want to go together like we used to?

244
00:10:26.126 --> 00:10:27.376
Sure. Dad.

245
00:10:27.377 --> 00:10:29.294
- Are you... Really?
- Whatever.

246
00:10:29.295 --> 00:10:31.380
I did not expect that answer.

247
00:10:31.381 --> 00:10:32.714
Okay. I have to get to class.

248
00:10:32.715 --> 00:10:34.299
- Okay. Yep.
- I love you. Lily?

249
00:10:34.300 --> 00:10:36.093
Do not smoke. it's not good for you.

250
00:10:36.094 --> 00:10:37.387
Yes.

251
00:10:42.475 --> 00:10:44.268
Mm!

252
00:10:44.269 --> 00:10:46.187
That's a cool shortcut.

253
00:10:53.069 --> 00:10:54.362
Whoa!

254
00:10:58.116 --> 00:11:00.200
Oh. that's a dangerous shortcut.

255
00:11:00.201 --> 00:11:01.452
Okay.

256
00:11:03.705 --> 00:11:06.206
- Hello! Hello. everybody.
- Woof!

257
00:11:06.207 --> 00:11:07.875
You look like Stone Hill got ya.

258
00:11:07.876 --> 00:11:11.545
Yeah. new shoes. and I forgot
to scuff up the bottom. so no biggie.

259
00:11:11.546 --> 00:11:12.921
Your leg is bleeding.

260
00:11:12.922 --> 00:11:14.548
Yeah. it doesn't hurt though.

261
00:11:14.549 --> 00:11:19.262
Okay. so I'm not sure
how many of you are familiar with my work.

262
00:11:20.346 --> 00:11:22.139
Ah. <i>Miami Amour.</i>

263
00:11:22.140 --> 00:11:25.684
That's a crowd-pleaser.
But I doubt that any of my books

264
00:11:25.685 --> 00:11:27.769
are on the shelves
of this hallowed institution.

265
00:11:27.770 --> 00:11:30.648
- They aren't.
- Oh. hey. I recognize you.

266
00:11:31.858 --> 00:11:35.777
Ah. okay.
They are called beach reads.

267
00:11:35.778 --> 00:11:39.948
And yes. you can usually
find them at the airport.

268
00:11:39.949 --> 00:11:43.411
But if you pick a good one.
you can't put it down.

269
00:11:44.120 --> 00:11:46.079
Welcome to "The Art of the Page-Turner."

270
00:11:46.080 --> 00:11:48.207
- Let's fucking go!
- Oh. yeah.

271
00:11:48.208 --> 00:11:50.375
Okay. so we're gonna start.

272
00:11:50.376 --> 00:11:54.963
I'm gonna talk about some of the authors
who made me want to tell stories.

273
00:11:54.964 --> 00:11:59.218
People like Greg McDonald.
or Sue Grafton. or Carl Hiaasen.

274
00:11:59.219 --> 00:12:00.802
Mine was Zadie Smith.

275
00:12:00.803 --> 00:12:04.599
Yes. Absolutely love him or her.

276
00:12:06.351 --> 00:12:07.726
Or they.

277
00:12:07.727 --> 00:12:12.105
I know it's a little uptight here.
so I would like you

278
00:12:12.106 --> 00:12:15.734
to call me Greg.

279
00:12:15.735 --> 00:12:17.569
- You wrote "Grg." bro.
- Hmm?

280
00:12:17.570 --> 00:12:18.696
The whiteboard. You wrote "Grg."

281
00:12:19.989 --> 00:12:21.240
And that's permanent marker.

282
00:12:21.241 --> 00:12:22.991
It's gonna say "Grg" all year.

283
00:12:22.992 --> 00:12:25.077
- Mr. Russo?
- Yes. question here.

284
00:12:25.078 --> 00:12:28.997
Is this supposed to be you?
'Cause if so. dude. nice washboard.

285
00:12:28.998 --> 00:12:30.415
No. no. no. that is not me.

286
00:12:30.416 --> 00:12:32.417
I have absolutely nothing
to do with the artwork.

287
00:12:32.418 --> 00:12:35.128
I read that you get approval
on all your cover art.

288
00:12:35.129 --> 00:12:37.381
- Did you. Ronni? You read that?
- Mm-hmm.

289
00:12:37.382 --> 00:12:40.050
Okay. You know. I...

290
00:12:40.051 --> 00:12:41.551
I emailed you all a syllabus

291
00:12:41.552 --> 00:12:46.265
and a breakdown of how every class
is going to go. minute by minute.

292
00:12:46.266 --> 00:12:48.225
Aw. man.
You made this sound like fun. man.

293
00:12:48.226 --> 00:12:49.476
This is not fun.

294
00:12:49.477 --> 00:12:51.478
I don't know any of these authors.

295
00:12:51.479 --> 00:12:54.898
I'm not sure if this literature
will speak to me.

296
00:12:54.899 --> 00:13:00.363
Oh. just you wait. Ronni.
You are going to be my white whale.

297
00:13:01.823 --> 00:13:05.575
At this institution. we have
zero tolerance for body shaming.

298
00:13:05.576 --> 00:13:08.203
Believe me. I was not shaming her.

299
00:13:08.204 --> 00:13:11.957
I was referencing a very famous book
that I have not read.

300
00:13:11.958 --> 00:13:13.625
<i>- Moby-Dick.</i>
- And besides.

301
00:13:13.626 --> 00:13:16.044
it doesn't really even make any sense.

302
00:13:16.045 --> 00:13:21.091
Ronni has a lovely figure.
No. no. Nope. Nope. Nope.

303
00:13:21.092 --> 00:13:23.719
If I may. Life's complicated.

304
00:13:23.720 --> 00:13:26.763
We all mess up.
We mess up at our jobs.

305
00:13:26.764 --> 00:13:28.349
Mess up at our relationships.

306
00:13:29.058 --> 00:13:35.022
But aren't we all trying our best
to navigate the complexities of this life?

307
00:13:35.023 --> 00:13:37.107
"The slings and arrows
of outrageous fortune."

308
00:13:37.108 --> 00:13:38.026
That's <i>Hamlet.</i> Greg.

309
00:13:38.985 --> 00:13:41.486
Personally. I think
that the quickest route

310
00:13:41.487 --> 00:13:44.239
back to forgiveness
is if we accept the fact

311
00:13:44.240 --> 00:13:45.867
that in our cores...

312
00:13:46.993 --> 00:13:48.243
we're just good people.

313
00:13:48.244 --> 00:13:50.663
You are a bad person and I hate you.

314
00:13:51.873 --> 00:13:53.582
I'm fine here with a verbal warning.

315
00:13:53.583 --> 00:13:56.085
- Oh. thank God.
- Walk with me. Mr. Russo.

316
00:13:57.879 --> 00:13:59.005
You're a bad boy.

317
00:14:06.679 --> 00:14:08.680
Ten years ago.
this school didn't even have

318
00:14:08.681 --> 00:14:10.557
- a disciplinary board.
- Mm.

319
00:14:10.558 --> 00:14:12.726
- It's a real gotcha culture now.
- The last thing I'd want to do

320
00:14:12.727 --> 00:14:14.978
- is make a young woman uncomfortable.
- Same.

321
00:14:14.979 --> 00:14:16.563
Yet we both keep doing it.

322
00:14:16.564 --> 00:14:18.774
Yeah. What?

323
00:14:18.775 --> 00:14:21.318
So. how are you getting on here?
You finding your bearings?

324
00:14:21.319 --> 00:14:23.820
Not even close. no.

325
00:14:23.821 --> 00:14:26.573
Tell you what. Greg.
Come by my place tonight.

326
00:14:26.574 --> 00:14:28.325
I'll give you the lay of the land.

327
00:14:28.326 --> 00:14:29.993
We can have a drink on the porch.

328
00:14:29.994 --> 00:14:32.371
I cannot tell you how much
I would love to do that.

329
00:14:32.372 --> 00:14:33.705
I have a great bottle of whiskey.

330
00:14:33.706 --> 00:14:34.956
Porch whiskey it is.

331
00:14:34.957 --> 00:14:36.250
- Look forward to it.
- Okay.

332
00:14:38.795 --> 00:14:40.670
- 'Kay.
- See you then.

333
00:14:40.671 --> 00:14:43.048
Not your mom! Not your milk!

334
00:14:43.049 --> 00:14:45.008
No more silence! End gun violence!

335
00:14:45.009 --> 00:14:47.594
Zoey. what is all this?

336
00:14:47.595 --> 00:14:49.513
They double-booked
the free speech zone.

337
00:14:49.514 --> 00:14:52.474
so on this side. we have vegans.
and on this side. we have gun control.

338
00:14:52.475 --> 00:14:54.643
- What side are you on?
- I haven't really decided yet.

339
00:14:54.644 --> 00:14:57.229
'cause on the one hand.
I do want jackfruit tacos in the caf.

340
00:14:57.230 --> 00:14:59.523
but I also don't love the idea
of getting shot.

341
00:14:59.524 --> 00:15:00.941
Tough call.

342
00:15:00.942 --> 00:15:02.901
The free speech zone
was over by Cabot Hall.

343
00:15:02.902 --> 00:15:04.778
Why is it outside my office now?

344
00:15:04.779 --> 00:15:06.656
I guess someone must have moved it.

345
00:15:08.408 --> 00:15:11.535
Anyway. I just wanted to say
thank you again for taking on Sunny.

346
00:15:11.536 --> 00:15:14.371
An '86 Molique Volnay!

347
00:15:14.372 --> 00:15:15.832
You must love your mistress very much.

348
00:15:17.208 --> 00:15:18.417
Well...

349
00:15:18.418 --> 00:15:19.835
We need to talk.

350
00:15:19.836 --> 00:15:21.671
I'm being summoned. Just give me a minute.

351
00:15:23.047 --> 00:15:26.091
Did you move the free speech zone
outside my office?

352
00:15:26.092 --> 00:15:28.218
You should thank me.

353
00:15:28.219 --> 00:15:30.512
I usually do more when people
complain about me to Walt.

354
00:15:30.513 --> 00:15:31.638
Oh. my God.

355
00:15:31.639 --> 00:15:33.723
Are you that petty?

356
00:15:33.724 --> 00:15:36.685
I'm gonna answer your question
with another question.

357
00:15:36.686 --> 00:15:37.728
Yes?

358
00:15:42.733 --> 00:15:44.067
Would you give me that water. please?

359
00:15:44.068 --> 00:15:45.318
No!

360
00:15:45.319 --> 00:15:48.029
You pompous prick.

361
00:15:48.030 --> 00:15:51.783
You are a walking relic of the past.

362
00:15:51.784 --> 00:15:53.410
and nobody's gonna miss you
when you're gone.

363
00:15:53.411 --> 00:15:55.996
Are you trying to be funny?
Don't you slide out of your chair!

364
00:15:55.997 --> 00:15:57.331
What are you doing?

365
00:15:57.999 --> 00:15:58.916
Riggs!

366
00:15:59.834 --> 00:16:01.334
- Call 9-1-1!
- What?

367
00:16:01.335 --> 00:16:03.170
- Cristle!
- Oh. my God!

368
00:16:03.171 --> 00:16:05.923
God. why do bad things
keep happening to me?

369
00:16:08.759 --> 00:16:10.427
<i>911. what's your emergency?</i>

370
00:16:10.428 --> 00:16:12.888
Hello. yes.
I'm just calling from Ludlow College.

371
00:16:12.889 --> 00:16:15.516
There's a man who I think
has maybe fainted.

372
00:16:16.767 --> 00:16:18.478
Well. I'm not a doctor.
but it doesn't look great.

373
00:16:27.403 --> 00:16:29.614
It's bad. You drive.

374
00:16:32.575 --> 00:16:33.576
Thank you.

375
00:16:35.453 --> 00:16:37.287
It was a heart attack.

376
00:16:37.288 --> 00:16:39.998
But Susan says he will pull through.

377
00:16:39.999 --> 00:16:41.791
Luckily. she has a friend
over there with her.

378
00:16:41.792 --> 00:16:42.792
Good. good.

379
00:16:42.793 --> 00:16:44.544
Did they say if a sip of water

380
00:16:44.545 --> 00:16:46.421
- would have made a difference?
- What?

381
00:16:46.422 --> 00:16:48.215
I've already taken care
of his classes for the week.

382
00:16:48.216 --> 00:16:49.841
but we need an interim Dean of Faculty.

383
00:16:49.842 --> 00:16:51.301
- Okay.
- Today.

384
00:16:51.302 --> 00:16:52.677
- Check.
- Then don't dilly-dally. do it.

385
00:16:52.678 --> 00:16:54.471
You're the one who's
preventing me from doing

386
00:16:54.472 --> 00:16:56.097
- what you want me to do.
- Fine.

387
00:16:56.098 --> 00:16:57.600
The show must go on.

388
00:16:58.392 --> 00:16:59.309
Position's yours.

389
00:16:59.310 --> 00:17:00.560
- No.
- You'll do great.

390
00:17:00.561 --> 00:17:01.895
- Congrats. Dylan!
- No. No. no. no.

391
00:17:01.896 --> 00:17:03.230
I'm not it. No. thank you.

392
00:17:03.231 --> 00:17:05.690
Well. it's a rule that goes back
to gladiator times.

393
00:17:05.691 --> 00:17:07.275
You kill a man. you get his job.

394
00:17:07.276 --> 00:17:08.652
I did not kill him.

395
00:17:08.653 --> 00:17:10.570
Well. the paramedics said
he was dead for three minutes.

396
00:17:10.571 --> 00:17:12.197
and you said that water thing
that was suspicious.

397
00:17:12.198 --> 00:17:16.535
Plus. you can show me how to do it all
with grace and sensitivity.

398
00:17:16.536 --> 00:17:18.287
I see what you're doing.

399
00:17:19.789 --> 00:17:20.830
Fine. I'm in.

400
00:17:20.831 --> 00:17:21.958
Congrats again. Dylan!

401
00:17:22.333 --> 00:17:24.501
- Appreciate you.
- That's the spirit.

402
00:17:24.502 --> 00:17:27.046
The man's an ox.
He'll be back before you know it.

403
00:17:32.134 --> 00:17:34.262
Have you ever seen him look so peaceful?

404
00:17:35.846 --> 00:17:37.013
No.

405
00:17:37.014 --> 00:17:39.391
He really valued your friendship.

406
00:17:39.392 --> 00:17:40.643
Yeah.

407
00:17:43.563 --> 00:17:45.856
V. Riggs. He's the best.

408
00:17:47.316 --> 00:17:50.485
- Ah. I should go.
- No. Please stay.

409
00:17:50.486 --> 00:17:52.195
Stay for Vincent.

410
00:17:52.196 --> 00:17:53.738
Vincent.

411
00:17:53.739 --> 00:17:58.994
Dean Riggs. who I call Vincent
because he is my friend.

412
00:17:58.995 --> 00:18:04.082
You know. he could sense
that I was feeling a little lost.

413
00:18:04.083 --> 00:18:05.918
and he reached out to me.

414
00:18:07.503 --> 00:18:09.005
Do you wanna hold his other hand?

415
00:18:10.715 --> 00:18:11.716
Okay.

416
00:18:20.725 --> 00:18:22.809
I want you all to close your eyes
and picture something.

417
00:18:22.810 --> 00:18:24.644
Go ahead. you can close your eyes.
Close your eyes. Okay.

418
00:18:24.645 --> 00:18:26.271
The year is 1929.

419
00:18:26.272 --> 00:18:28.189
- Are your eyes closed?
- Yeah. they're closed.

420
00:18:28.190 --> 00:18:31.568
Stalin. he sorta. he becomes
this kind of. this myth.

421
00:18:31.569 --> 00:18:33.446
Like the tooth fairy.

422
00:18:34.280 --> 00:18:36.824
if the tooth fairy
had led several violent purges.

423
00:18:39.118 --> 00:18:41.286
Stalin's cult of personality

424
00:18:41.287 --> 00:18:45.790
was equal parts power
and equal parts fear.

425
00:18:45.791 --> 00:18:46.792
Fear...

426
00:18:47.543 --> 00:18:49.044
- Oh!
- Oh. God. I'm so sorry.

427
00:18:49.045 --> 00:18:52.005
Oh gosh. Here. I'm sorry.
I owe you a drink.

428
00:18:52.006 --> 00:18:53.758
Not... No. I'm sorry.

429
00:18:55.926 --> 00:18:58.179
It'll probably go faster
without all those loop-de-dos.

430
00:18:59.305 --> 00:19:00.972
- Professor Shepard.
- Thanks.

431
00:19:00.973 --> 00:19:02.891
I hear it's Dean Shepard now.
Congratulations.

432
00:19:02.892 --> 00:19:04.267
- Yes. thank you.
- You're welcome.

433
00:19:04.268 --> 00:19:08.021
I recently submitted a proposal
for my new philosophy curriculum.

434
00:19:08.022 --> 00:19:10.106
Weeks ago. actually.
so I'm gonna need to hear back.

435
00:19:10.107 --> 00:19:11.566
like. ASAP. please.

436
00:19:11.567 --> 00:19:14.527
Wow. a philosophy emergency.
Don't get those a lot.

437
00:19:14.528 --> 00:19:15.987
I do.

438
00:19:15.988 --> 00:19:17.864
Let's give Dean Shepard a few days

439
00:19:17.865 --> 00:19:19.491
- to get her feet wet.
- Mm-hmm. teaching young people

440
00:19:19.492 --> 00:19:20.450
how to think.

441
00:19:20.451 --> 00:19:23.703
I could use that power for good.
or I could use it for something not good.

442
00:19:23.704 --> 00:19:26.206
They all want something.
so never give anyone your time

443
00:19:26.207 --> 00:19:27.875
- unless it's an emergency.
- Mm-hmm.

444
00:19:29.293 --> 00:19:31.420
Hi. What's up. Doc? No. what?

445
00:19:32.171 --> 00:19:36.675
Sorry. Is it... I know
I burned a house down. Ah!

446
00:19:36.676 --> 00:19:39.552
But if I don't have work
and I'm sitting at home.

447
00:19:39.553 --> 00:19:41.680
my mind is going to some dark
and crazy places.

448
00:19:41.681 --> 00:19:43.264
You threatening to strike again?

449
00:19:43.265 --> 00:19:46.351
No. no. no. No.

450
00:19:46.352 --> 00:19:48.645
- I should give her some time.
- Yeah. I think that would be best.

451
00:19:48.646 --> 00:19:50.438
- Let's go to my office.
- I'd love to.

452
00:19:50.439 --> 00:19:52.482
- Okay.
- Sorry.

453
00:19:52.483 --> 00:19:54.026
And. done.

454
00:19:59.824 --> 00:20:01.117
I let you sleep.

455
00:20:02.201 --> 00:20:03.911
You looked almost beautiful.

456
00:20:04.704 --> 00:20:06.413
Is it morning?

457
00:20:06.414 --> 00:20:08.790
Oh. no. no! I'm late. I'm late!

458
00:20:08.791 --> 00:20:10.251
Ah!

459
00:20:12.503 --> 00:20:14.462
I told myself I came to campus today

460
00:20:14.463 --> 00:20:16.548
- 'cause I missed being here.
- Mm.

461
00:20:16.549 --> 00:20:18.259
But I came to watch Arch teaching.

462
00:20:19.510 --> 00:20:21.052
Sorry. I don't know why
I'm telling you this.

463
00:20:21.053 --> 00:20:22.387
We don't even know each other that well.

464
00:20:22.388 --> 00:20:23.972
It's okay. Part of my job.

465
00:20:23.973 --> 00:20:25.515
- Really?
- I don't know.

466
00:20:25.516 --> 00:20:28.060
I met Archie two weeks
after I started teaching here.

467
00:20:29.186 --> 00:20:30.979
I don't really have friends of my own.

468
00:20:30.980 --> 00:20:32.856
Your dad's here now.
He could be your friend.

469
00:20:32.857 --> 00:20:34.691
Nope. I heard it.

470
00:20:34.692 --> 00:20:36.860
- My bad.
- I think I just need a win.

471
00:20:36.861 --> 00:20:40.280
So. is there any chance that
you would lift my suspension?

472
00:20:40.281 --> 00:20:43.575
Again. don't know how my job works.

473
00:20:43.576 --> 00:20:45.202
- but I'll try.
- Thank you.

474
00:20:47.037 --> 00:20:49.330
You should have seen him today in class.

475
00:20:49.331 --> 00:20:51.167
bouncing around all happy.

476
00:20:52.168 --> 00:20:53.919
Why isn't he struggling like I am?

477
00:21:03.220 --> 00:21:04.471
Hello. you. Hey.

478
00:21:04.472 --> 00:21:06.139
- You okay?
- Yeah.

479
00:21:06.140 --> 00:21:09.517
I was just looking at
some old photos of Roscoe.

480
00:21:09.518 --> 00:21:11.394
Thought you were gonna give that to Riggs.

481
00:21:11.395 --> 00:21:13.147
Sadly. I never got the chance.

482
00:21:14.023 --> 00:21:16.357
Well. I need an advisor
who can breathe on his own.

483
00:21:16.358 --> 00:21:18.526
So. I made a list of potential candidates

484
00:21:18.527 --> 00:21:21.362
and factored in
their professional connections

485
00:21:21.363 --> 00:21:23.282
relative to how likely they are to die.

486
00:21:24.200 --> 00:21:25.742
I crossed off two fatties and a smoker.

487
00:21:25.743 --> 00:21:27.994
That's quite morbid.

488
00:21:27.995 --> 00:21:29.537
I mean. it's only October. Sunny.

489
00:21:29.538 --> 00:21:31.372
- What's the rush?
- What's the rush?

490
00:21:31.373 --> 00:21:32.916
I've got a blueberry inside of me

491
00:21:32.917 --> 00:21:34.751
that's gonna grow to the size
of a fucking watermelon.

492
00:21:34.752 --> 00:21:36.961
So. it would "behoove" me
to lock in an internship

493
00:21:36.962 --> 00:21:39.756
before I start showing.
seeing as very few biotech companies

494
00:21:39.757 --> 00:21:41.966
want someone knocking over
beakers with a baby bump.

495
00:21:41.967 --> 00:21:44.010
Well. that... Hey.

496
00:21:44.011 --> 00:21:45.929
They can't actually discriminate
against you for that.

497
00:21:45.930 --> 00:21:47.972
- That is illegal.
- Great.

498
00:21:47.973 --> 00:21:49.725
I'll make a thousand citizen's arrests.

499
00:21:51.185 --> 00:21:53.813
You can go back to jacking off
to pictures of your gassy dog.

500
00:22:08.077 --> 00:22:09.202
Hold on. hold on. hold on!

501
00:22:09.203 --> 00:22:12.872
I'm here. No. no. Sit down. sit down.
Sit down. we're still having class.

502
00:22:12.873 --> 00:22:15.875
I don't have my lesson plan.

503
00:22:15.876 --> 00:22:18.211
Could someone go online
and check the syllabus?

504
00:22:18.212 --> 00:22:19.838
It is 10:46.

505
00:22:19.839 --> 00:22:21.798
What does it say
we should be doing right now?

506
00:22:21.799 --> 00:22:23.216
Five minutes of spirited discussion.

507
00:22:23.217 --> 00:22:26.469
Okay. does it say about what?

508
00:22:26.470 --> 00:22:29.014
"Reflections on what
we've discussed so far."

509
00:22:31.100 --> 00:22:32.308
Hm.

510
00:22:32.309 --> 00:22:33.978
You know what? Screw it.

511
00:22:35.604 --> 00:22:38.815
Let's just kick the ball around
a little bit. have some fun.

512
00:22:38.816 --> 00:22:42.652
- No one knows what that means.
- It is another metaphor. Ronni.

513
00:22:42.653 --> 00:22:46.739
Not unlike "white whale."
which I am saying directed at no one.

514
00:22:46.740 --> 00:22:48.074
Alright. here's the deal.

515
00:22:48.075 --> 00:22:52.287
I didn't take many
writing courses in college.

516
00:22:52.288 --> 00:22:53.746
partly because I didn't go to college.

517
00:22:53.747 --> 00:22:57.625
- Nice.
- I have written 11 bestsellers.

518
00:22:57.626 --> 00:23:02.630
and the idea of teaching here
is terrifying.

519
00:23:02.631 --> 00:23:05.592
All of you scare me. Except Spooner.

520
00:23:05.593 --> 00:23:07.635
- I got you. "Grg."
- But you know what?

521
00:23:07.636 --> 00:23:09.596
I think we have some things in common.

522
00:23:09.597 --> 00:23:11.723
We all love to tell stories.

523
00:23:11.724 --> 00:23:13.433
Why?

524
00:23:13.434 --> 00:23:15.060
Why do we want to write?

525
00:23:19.899 --> 00:23:22.442
Okay. I thought that
all that vulnerability

526
00:23:22.443 --> 00:23:26.030
might sort of loosen the jar.
but I will go first.

527
00:23:28.616 --> 00:23:30.993
The best thing about the <i>Rooster</i> books...

528
00:23:31.911 --> 00:23:35.414
is that he gets to do everything
I wish I could.

529
00:23:36.332 --> 00:23:39.292
Get in a bar fight.
or break the girl's heart.

530
00:23:39.293 --> 00:23:42.545
Honestly. I write because sometimes.

531
00:23:42.546 --> 00:23:44.381
I wish I was someone else.

532
00:23:49.094 --> 00:23:52.639
When I used to write in high school.
it was like the only time I felt smart.

533
00:23:52.640 --> 00:23:54.474
Thank you. Tommy.

534
00:23:54.475 --> 00:23:55.476
Anybody else?

535
00:23:56.226 --> 00:23:57.977
I started writing after
my parents got divorced.

536
00:23:57.978 --> 00:23:59.354
Okay.

537
00:23:59.355 --> 00:24:02.649
Now. I write a lot of sad stories
about horses who love their kids.

538
00:24:02.650 --> 00:24:05.443
Beautiful!
That's great creativity. Maya!

539
00:24:05.444 --> 00:24:06.403
Oh!

540
00:24:08.113 --> 00:24:10.823
I am so. so sorry.

541
00:24:10.824 --> 00:24:13.117
I blame the shoes.

542
00:24:13.118 --> 00:24:15.244
I actually got rid of 'em.

543
00:24:15.245 --> 00:24:17.121
- Good. They were too shiny.
- Oh.

544
00:24:17.122 --> 00:24:18.831
I've never run one of these things.

545
00:24:18.832 --> 00:24:20.208
So. what happens next?

546
00:24:20.209 --> 00:24:22.043
We have to go through the complaint.

547
00:24:22.044 --> 00:24:24.170
Okay. it says here you closed your hand

548
00:24:24.171 --> 00:24:25.923
firmly around her breast?

549
00:24:28.884 --> 00:24:31.594
I think "firmly" is an exaggeration.

550
00:24:31.595 --> 00:24:34.974
It was more of a soft and gentle cupping.

551
00:24:36.141 --> 00:24:38.352
Why did I put it like that?

552
00:24:39.853 --> 00:24:43.272
Miss Samuels acknowledges
it was an accident.

553
00:24:43.273 --> 00:24:45.525
Yeah. I was bracing my fall.

554
00:24:45.526 --> 00:24:47.736
and her breasts
happened to take the brace.

555
00:24:48.487 --> 00:24:50.989
Okay. Don't do it again.

556
00:24:50.990 --> 00:24:53.491
I'm out. Alright.

557
00:24:53.492 --> 00:24:55.369
Thank you. everybody. Appreciate it.

558
00:25:01.125 --> 00:25:02.333
Walter?

559
00:25:02.334 --> 00:25:03.918
Hello. hi. Sorry. have you got a moment?

560
00:25:03.919 --> 00:25:06.922
You have anything problematic in your life
you still have a soft spot for?

561
00:25:08.382 --> 00:25:10.717
Michael Jackson?
Woody Allen? Plastic straws?

562
00:25:10.718 --> 00:25:12.927
Probably be Roald Dahl for me.

563
00:25:12.928 --> 00:25:15.054
Not great with our
Jewish friends. but I mean.

564
00:25:15.055 --> 00:25:16.598
<i>Matilda the Musical.</i> oh. come on.

565
00:25:17.766 --> 00:25:19.767
Listen. I know that
you only take on advisees

566
00:25:19.768 --> 00:25:21.811
if you feel that you have
a particular sort of connection.

567
00:25:21.812 --> 00:25:23.229
If you just... Sunny?

568
00:25:23.230 --> 00:25:25.481
Could I borrow you for a second. please?

569
00:25:25.482 --> 00:25:28.693
Sunny here is a fantastic
neuroscience candidate.

570
00:25:28.694 --> 00:25:30.820
centering particularly on
physical fitness and well-being.

571
00:25:30.821 --> 00:25:33.239
Two fiery passions of yours.
if I'm not mistaken.

572
00:25:33.240 --> 00:25:34.741
I mean. how...
Listen. you know. you could...

573
00:25:34.742 --> 00:25:36.993
You could take your advisory
sessions in the sauna.

574
00:25:36.994 --> 00:25:38.786
- You know?
- Aren't you pregnant?

575
00:25:38.787 --> 00:25:41.539
In Nordic countries. it's actually routine
throughout pregnancy.

576
00:25:41.540 --> 00:25:44.125
And worst-case scenario.
we just keep the temp below 170.

577
00:25:44.126 --> 00:25:46.711
You know. I always see you
with a protein drink.

578
00:25:46.712 --> 00:25:48.254
and I make my own.

579
00:25:48.255 --> 00:25:49.256
If you...

580
00:25:50.174 --> 00:25:52.467
You'll taste pea proteins and a little bit

581
00:25:52.468 --> 00:25:55.094
of dehydrated cherry
for flavors and antioxidants.

582
00:25:55.095 --> 00:25:56.305
That's incredible.

583
00:25:58.057 --> 00:25:59.224
I'll leave you to it.

584
00:26:01.852 --> 00:26:04.353
You're sure you're okay with me
having a front row seat

585
00:26:04.354 --> 00:26:05.938
to your interpersonal drama?

586
00:26:05.939 --> 00:26:07.941
I would actually love a third-party POV.

587
00:26:08.692 --> 00:26:11.361
Oh. I think we could have
a great deal of fun with this.

588
00:26:15.240 --> 00:26:18.911
Don't be afraid to move it!
Don't be afraid to move it!

589
00:26:23.290 --> 00:26:24.333
Okay.

590
00:26:25.125 --> 00:26:27.210
Oh. sorry.

591
00:26:27.211 --> 00:26:29.629
- Hi. Dad.
- <i>Hey. where are you?</i>

592
00:26:29.630 --> 00:26:30.880
<i>You need to get down here.</i>

593
00:26:30.881 --> 00:26:32.673
The new coach is drinking a beer.

594
00:26:32.674 --> 00:26:34.509
and during the last timeout.

595
00:26:34.510 --> 00:26:37.178
he was singing <i>Sweet Caroline</i> to nobody.

596
00:26:37.179 --> 00:26:40.139
I actually ended up going out with Lily
and some of her friends.

597
00:26:40.140 --> 00:26:42.183
So. you're not coming?

598
00:26:42.184 --> 00:26:46.020
Oh. shoot. Well. I was excited
to tell you about class.

599
00:26:46.021 --> 00:26:49.649
I tried that thing of yours.
You know. the kicking the ball around.

600
00:26:49.650 --> 00:26:53.569
That's so great. Can I call you back?
I'm actually having kind of a fun time.

601
00:26:53.570 --> 00:26:56.155
Sure. I'll just watch the game by myself.

602
00:26:56.156 --> 00:26:58.616
Maybe there is a daughter here
without a dad.

603
00:26:58.617 --> 00:27:00.993
<i>Please don't make me feel guilty
for not hanging out with you.</i>

604
00:27:00.994 --> 00:27:03.496
You took this job without
asking how I felt about it.

605
00:27:03.497 --> 00:27:05.248
You did that for you.

606
00:27:05.249 --> 00:27:10.503
Yeah. I did that for me.
I am a selfish guy. Selfish Greg.

607
00:27:10.504 --> 00:27:12.630
<i>Well. have fun with Lily.</i>

608
00:27:12.631 --> 00:27:14.882
And honey. remember what
they say about secondhand smoke.

609
00:27:14.883 --> 00:27:16.425
It's even worse than firsthand smoke.

610
00:27:16.426 --> 00:27:17.845
Okay. Love you.

611
00:27:20.180 --> 00:27:21.430
Here we go. blue!

612
00:27:21.431 --> 00:27:22.933
Paluso. come here.

613
00:27:24.434 --> 00:27:27.061
Ah. finally. a friendly face.

614
00:27:27.062 --> 00:27:30.273
Speaking of friendly faces.
who's that happy fella?

615
00:27:30.274 --> 00:27:33.985
Oh. this is my jersey from when
I played minor league hockey

616
00:27:33.986 --> 00:27:35.403
with the Ontario Indians.

617
00:27:35.404 --> 00:27:38.823
Woo-woo-woo! Chief love hockey.

618
00:27:38.824 --> 00:27:41.659
Oh. my God.
I have to take this off. don't I?

619
00:27:41.660 --> 00:27:43.703
- I would.
- Oh. Oh. sh... Okay.

620
00:27:43.704 --> 00:27:45.037
Oh. my God.

621
00:27:45.038 --> 00:27:48.541
How hard is it for you
to stop offending people?

622
00:27:48.542 --> 00:27:50.419
It's harder than you think.

623
00:27:52.379 --> 00:27:55.548
There we go.
You can still see the feathers. Damn it.

624
00:27:55.549 --> 00:28:00.887
Ten minutes ago. I was in my bed.
in my bonnet. with my tea.

625
00:28:00.888 --> 00:28:03.848
And then. I get a call saying
that as part of my new job.

626
00:28:03.849 --> 00:28:08.769
that I gotta drive down here
and reprimand our drunk hockey coach.

627
00:28:08.770 --> 00:28:11.230
Well. he might not be drunk.
but he is definitely buzzed.

628
00:28:11.231 --> 00:28:13.275
Come here. real quick.
I gotta tell you something.

629
00:28:14.401 --> 00:28:17.112
Be better! Be better!

630
00:28:18.071 --> 00:28:20.114
- He's drunk.
- I don't wanna police him.

631
00:28:20.115 --> 00:28:21.532
I don't want to police you.

632
00:28:21.533 --> 00:28:23.743
I am begging you. please.

633
00:28:23.744 --> 00:28:26.037
Get your shit together.

634
00:28:26.038 --> 00:28:29.081
I'm trying. it's just
nothing here makes sense.

635
00:28:29.082 --> 00:28:31.042
My daughter doesn't want me to be around.

636
00:28:31.043 --> 00:28:33.377
And I keep falling down hills.

637
00:28:33.378 --> 00:28:35.880
Walt's assistant is creeping me out.

638
00:28:35.881 --> 00:28:37.798
- I don't have time for this.
- No.

639
00:28:37.799 --> 00:28:41.344
Because you are busy.
and I envy you for that.

640
00:28:41.345 --> 00:28:43.638
I have so much time on my hands

641
00:28:43.639 --> 00:28:46.265
that I got to read that book
that your friend Ruby wrote.

642
00:28:46.266 --> 00:28:48.684
And it is not my thing. honey.

643
00:28:48.685 --> 00:28:50.437
Don't snap. Greg.

644
00:28:51.230 --> 00:28:52.730
You know. everybody says college

645
00:28:52.731 --> 00:28:54.858
is the best time of your life.
but I think it stinks.

646
00:28:57.444 --> 00:28:58.862
I wanna go home.

647
00:29:00.072 --> 00:29:02.240
You sound like a college freshman.

648
00:29:02.241 --> 00:29:04.116
Oh. yeah.

649
00:29:04.117 --> 00:29:05.285
But you're not.

650
00:29:06.286 --> 00:29:07.537
You're 60.

651
00:29:08.705 --> 00:29:11.792
You want to go? Go.

652
00:29:12.793 --> 00:29:15.629
I'm 57. And you're mean.

653
00:29:17.798 --> 00:29:19.924
Come on! Go!

654
00:29:19.925 --> 00:29:22.886
Yeah! Yeah!

655
00:29:30.936 --> 00:29:33.938
So good! Everybody! So good!

656
00:29:33.939 --> 00:29:35.398
So good!

657
00:29:35.399 --> 00:29:38.485
Aw. you guys fuckin' suck balls!

658
00:29:40.821 --> 00:29:42.447
Oh. fuck. who cares? Play on!

659
00:30:56.688 --> 00:30:58.607
<i>Bye-bye.</i>

